      "content": "It's basically a hybrid approach. It uses hard-coded logic rules to prevent those weird linguistic hallucinations and keeps things super consistent. The dev team says it's much more efficient on the hardware, too. We're basically moving away from the pure LLM architecture because it's too unpredictable for the high-stakes stuff.",
